title: The Widows' House
creator: Sarah Orne Jewett
source: Librivox recording of a public-domain text
description: LibriVox rvolunteers bring you 12 recordings of The Widows' House by Sarah Orne Jewett. This was the Fortnightly Poetry project for November 11, 2012. Sarah Orne Jewett was an American novelist and short story writer, best known for her local color works set along or near the southern seacoast of Maine. (Summary from Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. Download M4B (12MB)
subject: librivox; literature; audiobook; poetry; nature; philosophy; religion
